<https://sanskrit-lexicon.github.io/csl-standards/id/case/mw-pwg-pwk%3Aka#sense-mw-1> a ontolex:LexicalSense ;
  ontolex:isSenseOf <https://sanskrit-lexicon.github.io/csl-standards/id/case/mw-pwg-pwk%3Aka> ;
  csl:sourceDictionary "mw" ;
  skos:definition "is occasionally used alone as an indefinite pronoun, especially in negative sentences ( e.g., no one is a favourite of any one"@en .

<https://sanskrit-lexicon.github.io/csl-standards/id/case/mw-pwg-pwk%3Aka#sense-mw-2> a ontolex:LexicalSense ;
  ontolex:isSenseOf <https://sanskrit-lexicon.github.io/csl-standards/id/case/mw-pwg-pwk%3Aka> ;
  csl:sourceDictionary "mw" ;
  skos:definition "no one else knows"@en .

<https://sanskrit-lexicon.github.io/csl-standards/id/case/mw-pwg-pwk%3Aka#sense-mw-3> a ontolex:LexicalSense ;
  ontolex:isSenseOf <https://sanskrit-lexicon.github.io/csl-standards/id/case/mw-pwg-pwk%3Aka> ;
  csl:sourceDictionary "mw" ;
  skos:definition "how does he kill any one?) Generally, however, is only made indefinite when connected with the particles,,,, and, in which case may sometimes be preceded by the relative ( e.g., any persons whatsoever"@en .

<https://sanskrit-lexicon.github.io/csl-standards/id/case/mw-pwg-pwk%3Aka#sense-mw-4> a ontolex:LexicalSense ;
  ontolex:isSenseOf <https://sanskrit-lexicon.github.io/csl-standards/id/case/mw-pwg-pwk%3Aka> ;
  csl:sourceDictionary "mw" ;
  skos:definition "to any deity whatsoever"@en .

<https://sanskrit-lexicon.github.io/csl-standards/id/case/mw-pwg-pwk%3Aka#sense-mw-5> a ontolex:LexicalSense ;
  ontolex:isSenseOf <https://sanskrit-lexicon.github.io/csl-standards/id/case/mw-pwg-pwk%3Aka> ;
  csl:sourceDictionary "mw" ;
  skos:definition "any friends whatsoever"@en .

<https://sanskrit-lexicon.github.io/csl-standards/id/case/mw-pwg-pwk%3Aka#sense-mw-6> a ontolex:LexicalSense ;
  ontolex:isSenseOf <https://sanskrit-lexicon.github.io/csl-standards/id/case/mw-pwg-pwk%3Aka> ;
  csl:sourceDictionary "mw" ;
  skos:definition "whatever). The particle, being composed of and, properly gives a negative force to the pronoun ( e.g., without which there is nothing), but the negative sense is generally dropped ( e.g., any one"@en .

<https://sanskrit-lexicon.github.io/csl-standards/id/case/mw-pwg-pwk%3Aka#sense-mw-7> a ontolex:LexicalSense ;
  ontolex:isSenseOf <https://sanskrit-lexicon.github.io/csl-standards/id/case/mw-pwg-pwk%3Aka> ;
  csl:sourceDictionary "mw" ;
  skos:definition "no one), and a relative is sometimes connected with it ( e.g., anything whatsoever). Examples of with the interrogative are common"@en .

<https://sanskrit-lexicon.github.io/csl-standards/id/case/mw-pwg-pwk%3Aka#sense-mw-8> a ontolex:LexicalSense ;
  ontolex:isSenseOf <https://sanskrit-lexicon.github.io/csl-standards/id/case/mw-pwg-pwk%3Aka> ;
  csl:sourceDictionary "mw" ;
  skos:definition "and are not so common, but the latter is often found in ( e.g., any one"@en .

